type of points
==============
1.border points
2.core points
3.noise points
4.density connected points

A core point is a point whose epsilon neighbourhood has more points than min points.
A border point is a point whose epsilon neighbourhood has at least one core point but less points than min points.
A point which is neither border points or core point is called noise point.

Density connected points
========================
if two points are connected to each other through core points and any two core points are at distance <= epsilon
Density connected points belong to the same cluster.



Algorithm
=========
1.Identify core point,border point,noise point 
2.For all unclustered core point
   1.Create a new cluster
   2.Add all points that are unclustered and desnsity connected to the current point into this cluster
3.For all the unclustered and border point assign it to the cluster of nearest core.
4.Leave all the noise point as it is.



